The police are on the hunt for six men who robbed a McDonald's franchise in Johannesburg earlier in July. CCTV footage of the incident shows the men entering the franchise in Bruma one by one, before approaching customers and employees. According to police spokesperson Captain Johan Jordaan, five customers were instructed to lie on the ground. "The manager was then ordered to open the safe and an amount of R18 000 as well as a customer's cellphone was taken." MORE |Â WATCH: Unfazed Joburg customer sips on juice box as armed men rob store Jordaan told News24 one of the suspects was armed and nobody was injured. The police are using the CCTV footage to assist in their investigation. A case of business robbery was opened at the Cleveland police station and no arrests have been made. GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here.KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 